{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Models are trained for 10 epochs with instance shuffling in each epoch.",
    "Implementation DetailsAll experiments are implemented in PyTorch [62] and conducted on a computing platform equipped with an AMD EPYC 7542 CPU (2.9GHz), 94 GB of RAM, and an NVIDIA RTX 4090 GPU.",
    "For the real-world ANA dataset, we adopt the Adam optimizer [63] with β = (0.9, 0.999), a learning rate of 5 × 10 -3, and a batch size of 32.",
    "All backbone networks are pre-trained on ImageNet [64], and input patches of size 448 × 448 are resized to match the input dimensions of the corresponding models.For the three real-world multi-label medical image datasets, we follow a unified hyperparameter protocol across all competing methods unless otherwise specified in their original implementations.",
    "In our setup, each image is divided into smaller patches of approximately 64 ×64 pixels, with the total number of instances per image determined by its resolution."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Implementation DetailsAll experiments are implemented in PyTorch [62] and conducted on a computing platform equipped with an AMD EPYC 7542 CPU (2.9GHz), 94 GB of RAM, and an NVIDIA RTX 4090 GPU.",
    "For the real-world ANA dataset, we adopt the Adam optimizer [63] with β = (0.9, 0.999), a learning rate of 5 × 10 -3, and a batch size of 32.",
    "All backbone networks are pre-trained on ImageNet [64], and input patches of size 448 × 448 are resized to match the input dimensions of the corresponding models.For the three real-world multi-label medical image datasets, we follow a unified hyperparameter protocol across all competing methods unless otherwise specified in their original implementations."
